* :C2u2diaM9tC7rfXZ: "In his classic 1948 paper, Yakovlev reduced behavior to movement (which it fundamentally is) and conceived 'three spheres of motility' comprising (1) movements in the internal milieu, which he called visceration, (2) the physical expression of internal states (emotion), and (3) manipulation of the external world (effectuation)."
